column1: This format can optimize Theta H value, as well as calculate Psi(50) and sigma values automatically
First add "Solver" to your excel. For example in Excel 2007, you can find Solver under "Data/Analysis". It is an add-in that may need to be loaded
1.Click "Solver", you will see a window pop out.
2. To estimate Theta H, type "$I$4" in "Set Objective", choose "MAX", and type "$I$3" in "by changing variable cells"
3. Click "solve", then the optimized Theta H and R2 will be calculated.
4. For Psi(50) and sigma values: click L5, select your data range in F and G column; also do the same for L6.Then Psib(50) and sigma values will be calculated shown in cell I5 and I6
